[2]
Date: Sat 2 Nov 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source Way More Sports, Associated Press report, Fri 1 Nov 2002 [edited]
<http://waymoresports.thestar.com/NASApp/cs/ContentServer?pagename=waymoresports/Layout/Article_Type1&c=Article&cid=1035773912627&call_page=WM_Soccer&call_pageid=979744613060&call_pagepath=MoreSports/Soccer>

Scotland: Viral Outbreak Threatens Scottish Soccer
--------------------------------------------------
An outbreak of [viral gastroenteritis] is sweeping through Scottish soccer.
The [virus infection] forced Scottish officials to call off a League Cup
game on Wed 30 Oct 2002 at Aberdeen against Motherwell. And the outbreak
briefly put question marks around Sunday's Aberdeen at match at Celtic
Park, Glasgow, and perhaps another game on Sun 3 Nov 2002 between Edinburgh
rivals Hibernian and Hearts. Hibernian was the last club to play at
Aberdeen. The Aberdeen-Celtic match was eventually given the go-ahead on
Friday with Aberdeen saying the situation had [improved]. "Things have
improved greatly and only 5 players have been sent home today," a club
spokesman said.
